subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. 

Parvoscincus aurorus


sp. nov.

can be identified by the following combination of characters: (
1
) A small body size (SVL at maturity 
39.5–46.6 mm
); (
2
) MBSR = 
31–35
; (
3
) PV = 
65–75
; (
4
) dorsal scales nonstriated without apical pits; (
5
) apical pits on hind limbs, none on forelimbs; (
6
) four enlarged supraoculars; (
7
) anterior loreal single; (
8
) three preoculars; (
9
) and 
15–17
Toe IV SDL.
